==English==
===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[محمد]]}} (''muħámmad'', [[praise]]d, [[commendable]], [[laudable]]), the past participle of {{ARchar|[[حمد]]}} (''ħámida'', to [[praise]], [[commend]], [[laud]], [[extol]]).

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Muhammad'''

# The [[prophet]] who [[founded]] [[Islam]].
# A male given name, esp. in Islamic culture.

